{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Impose restrictions on benefits and allowances for former Prime Ministers",
        "additional_details": "Following a series of short terms served by unelected (by the public) PM's during recent years, and a former Prime Minister being found to have misled the House of Commons this change needs to happen.",
        "background": "Former Prime Ministers are entitled to benefits such as the Ministerial Severance Pay and the Public Duties Cost Allowance currently set at a limit of \u00a3115,000 per year. Only those who have served a minimum 1-year term and not been sanctioned by the House of Commons should qualify for this.",
